<p>WHAT CAN I DO ABOUT MY MASK RASH? </p>

<p>We've heard a lot about 'maskne' recently — break-outs caused by wearing a face covering — but some people suffer instead from irritated, itchy skin under their masks.</p>

<p>'If you notice an itchy, red rash rather than pimples, you may have contact dermatitis,' says cosmetic scientist Lynne Sanders, founder of Cosmetics A La Carte.</p>

<p>'Consider protecting your skin with a barrier cream. In my view, the best option is Vaseline.'</p>

<p>Vaseline Original should be applied before you put on your mask</p>

<p>boots.com </p>

<p>Then use a gentle cleanser, such as Cosmetics A La Carte Total Lift Off, and moisturiser when you get home.  </p>

<p>cosmeticsalacarte.com </p>

