<p>SHAMELESS INDULGENCE </p>

<p>Building on the success of Lancome's citrussy floral fragrance Idole, the new, more flamboyant Idole L'Intense takes the key themes of rose, jasmine and chypre notes and turns up the sensuality.</p>

<p>Honeyed Grasse rose absolute combines with the fresh, green fragrance of Isparta rose petal essence to create the floral background. </p>

<p>Layered with a musky jasmine trio, with light hints of fruit, patchouli, cedar, sandalwood and Madagascar bourbon vanilla, it's a heady, exotic scent that is less feminine than feminist. </p>

<p>Lancome makes no bones about the fact it is squarely aimed at 'leaders and innovators of tomorrow'.</p>

<p>So if you're 'strong', 'outspoken' and 'empowered', this may well be the perfume for you.</p>

<p>lancome.co.uk </p>
